  "lastUpdatedOn": "2013-06-04",
  "religion": "Collins was raised a strict Southern Baptist, but is now a fan and follower of all spiritual forms of belief.",
  "politicalViews": "Collins is a liberal.",
  "author": "Tom Kershaw",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Lynn Collins was born in Houston, Texas. She grew up there and in Singapore and Japan."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Collins was raised a strict Southern Baptist. But it would seem that exposure to the culture of New York City drastically changed her perspective. She said:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4,
      "parentId": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "My family are very, very religious in Texas. They're Southern Baptists. I left to go to New York when I was 17 and I realised I wasn't Southern Baptist. That's not how I am inclined.",
      "sourceTitle": "Down to earth with the most beautiful woman in the universe",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.independent.ie/woman/celeb-news/down-to-earth-with-the-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-universe-26834023.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "This began a journey of spiritual discovery for Collins in which she discovered a holistic, unified approach to religion:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 7,
      "parentId": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I started studying all different religions and all different beliefs — mysticism, paganism, everything. I got to a place a few years ago where I realised that, to me, they're all the same thing.",
      "sourceTitle": "Down to earth with the most beautiful woman in the universe",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.independent.ie/woman/celeb-news/down-to-earth-with-the-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-universe-26834023.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Her"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "link",
      "text": "Twitter feed",
      "sourceUrl": "https://twitter.com/lynncollins7"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "confirms this pan-religious view, with tweets and retweets about everything from conventional Christianity to Dalai Lama quotes to healing crystals to palmistry. She is indeed a meta-religious person, and most likely very spiritual.",
      "parentId": 8
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Left-leaning diversity"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Collins' politics seem constrained entirely within her Twitter feed. But what a gold mine! She appears to be more on the Democrat/liberal side of things. She signaled her support of both Obama and gun control when she retweeted this Obama message:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 12,
      "parentId": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 12,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "FACT: Since 1968, more Americans have died from gun violence than in all of America's wars—combined. #DemandAction",
      "sourceTitle": "lynn collins (lynncollins7) on Twitter. Twitter",
      "sourceUrl": "https://twitter.com/lynncollins7"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "She's tweeted about animal rights, environmentalism and fracking, and gay rights when she tweeted a Human Rights Campaign message:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 15,
      "parentId": 14
    },
    {
      "parentId": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "\"Love knows no religion. Love knows no color. Love knows no gender.\" Wade Henderson #UnitedForMarriage",
      "sourceTitle": "lynn collins (lynncollins7) on Twitter. Twitter",
      "sourceUrl": "https://twitter.com/lynncollins7"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "parentId": 16,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Plus, she backhandedly criticized the Catholic Church and expressed her affinity to feminism when she retweeted a satirical message from the editor of the"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 16,
      "type": "emphasis",
      "text": "Daily Beast"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "during deliberations for a new Pope:",
      "parentId": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 17
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 18,
      "parentId": 17
    },
    {
      "parentId": 18,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Unchanged stance on gays, contraception & women? We gotta have a nun as next pope. No change til pink smoke billows @ #Vatican #PopeFrancis",
      "sourceTitle": "lynn collins (lynncollins7) on Twitter. Twitter",
      "sourceUrl": "https://twitter.com/lynncollins7"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 19
    },
    {
      "parentId": 19,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Clearly, she's quite liberal."
    }
  ],
